&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Prophecy&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;The leader in AI-native data preparation and analysis, Prophecy is revolutionizing how the world’s top enterprises turn data chaos into reliable insights. We introduce the AI-native data lifecycle (generate, refine, deploy) where our industry leading AI agents and humans work hand-in-hand in visual and document interfaces to analyze, transform and prepare data, to ship trusted insights at enterprise scale. To learn more, visit us on &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/company/prophecy-ai/posts/?feedView=all&quot;&gt;LinkedIn&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;You&#39;ll own the intelligence layer at Prophecy: the AI systems that let our agents understand data schemas, generate correct transformations, and reason over enterprise knowledge. This isn&#39;t a role where you implement someone else&#39;s spec — you make the calls on agent architecture, model selection, quality evaluation, and build vs. buy. The scope scales with you; strong engineers have enormous leverage here regardless of title.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Own&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agent design and quality.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Architect multi-step AI agents end-to-end — problem decomposition, context retrieval, error recovery, output quality. Set the bar, build the evals, own the improvement loop.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Retrieval and knowledge systems.&lt;/strong&gt; Own the RAG pipelines, vector and graph-based retrieval, and knowledge representations that let agents reason accurately over customer schemas, lineage, and semantics.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Code generation and data transformation.&lt;/strong&gt; Own the AI layer behind Prophecy&#39;s core capability — natural language to production-grade transformations: prompt design, model selection, fine-tuning, output validation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Production AI.&lt;/strong&gt; Make AI that works in the lab work at scale — latency, throughput, observability, knowing when to optimize a model vs. restructure a system.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;You&#39;ve built coding agents or AI systems in production and owned them when things break. You think in failure modes and evaluation strategy, not capability demos. You make architectural decisions under uncertainty and know when to move fast versus when to do it right.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;You&#39;re a builder who loves picking up new technologies — in a field where last year&#39;s best practice may already be obsolete, that instinct matters. You have a strong perspective on how coding agents should work and bring it to design discussions, not just implementation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Experience level is flexible; what matters is the track record. We&#39;d expect 4–6+ years in software engineering with meaningful AI/ML depth.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;Stack and Background We Value&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
